node.title: 'I'm heartbroken': Tributes flow for Michael Nesmith, musician and star of The Monkees TV show
node.description: Michael Nesmith, one of the stars of The Monkees, a 1960s TV comedy series about a rock quartet modelled after the Beatles, dies of natural causes at the age of 78.

node.title: ‘There’s a dignity in being taken seriously’: First Nations books find home in innovative program
node.description: In the decade since black&write! began, it has shepherded acclaimed works by First Nations writers including Nardi Simpson, Ali Cobby Eckermann and Claire G. Coleman.

node.title: T-Mobile joins employers paying at least $20 an hour
node.description: Wireless carrier says number of applicants for customer service jobs spiked after it began paying workers more.

node.title: How Bank Regulators Are Trying to Oust a Trump Holdover
node.description: Jelena McWilliams, the FDIC’s chairwoman, doesn’t always go along with President Biden’s agenda. Other regulators want to push her out.
